1
00:00:00,041 --> 00:00:04,541
Of course, when they took you to the judge, your eyes were blindfolded and they would lift the blindfold in front of the judge

2
00:00:06,916 --> 00:00:09,291
He said, You're before the judge

3
00:00:10,666 --> 00:00:16,250
He started by asking me about prayer and about religion, and there was a group sitting beside him

4
00:00:18,125 --> 00:00:22,416
Interviewer: What kind of questions did he ask you?

5
00:00:22,500 --> 00:00:25,125
About prayer, Do you pray? I answered, Yes

6
00:00:25,916 --> 00:00:28,250
I told him, Yes. He said, Do you know how to recite the call to prayer? I told him, Yes

7
00:00:28,416 --> 00:00:31,625
He said—Get up and recite the call to prayer. I tried the call to prayer, but I didn't do it well

8
00:00:32,458 --> 00:00:34,750
He said—This one didn't use to pray, he was lying to us

9
00:00:36,750 --> 00:00:43,250
He said—He must learn the call to prayer and the prayer, and so on

10
00:00:43,708 --> 00:00:47,625
He would ask you with a hard stare when he spoke to you

11
00:00:48,166 --> 00:00:52,041
In a way that makes you afraid even of yourself

12
00:00:56,583 --> 00:00:58,500
No, he is the one who asks you about this

13
00:01:00,375 --> 00:01:03,375
Interviewer: During your interrogation, especially the first interrogation

14
00:01:03,791 --> 00:01:07,791
Did you feel he knew information about your life?

15
00:01:08,041 --> 00:01:10,625
Did he mention any details that no one knew except you and your family?

16
00:01:10,791 --> 00:01:14,833
No, he knew this, but he didn't say it directly

17
00:01:14,916 --> 00:01:15,958
Interviewer: How did you know that?

18
00:01:16,166 --> 00:01:21,583
I mean, it was obvious, he would ask you questions like, You meet with so-and-so, or you go to such-and-such a place

19
00:01:22,708 --> 00:01:26,041
He had information, but who supplied him with it, I don't know

20
00:01:26,500 --> 00:01:30,833
But he told me at that time—This is your last warning

21
00:01:30,958 --> 00:01:33,958
But next time, the punishment will be different

22
00:01:34,291 --> 00:01:38,791
He threatened me, and after I got out I was under surveillance

23
00:01:39,708 --> 00:01:43,416
Whenever I went anywhere, there were one or two people watching me

24
00:01:43,541 --> 00:01:45,833
And in the end, I was being watched

25
00:01:45,916 --> 00:01:51,625
But in the end, I left Iraq

26
00:01:52,750 --> 00:01:54,416
Interviewer: About the judge who was interrogating you

27
00:01:54,791 --> 00:01:56,208
And since you were the one who shaved his hair

28
00:01:56,333 --> 00:01:57,750
Can you describe his features for us?

29
00:01:58,041 --> 00:02:00,375
And about how old he was, his appearance, and the clothes he wore?

30
00:02:00,500 --> 00:02:03,083
As for clothes, he wore black and a black turban

31
00:02:03,666 --> 00:02:08,250
And his beard was like this, and his age was between forty and forty-one, or about forty-two years

32
00:02:08,500 --> 00:02:10,083
Interviewer: Was his dialect Standard Arabic or the dialect of Mosul?

33
00:02:10,291 --> 00:02:12,333
No, no, the dialect was different, he wasn't from Mosul

34
00:02:13,166 --> 00:02:15,000
Interviewer: Standard Arabic or rural? Witness: No, rural

35
00:02:16,500 --> 00:02:17,583
Interviewer: Meaning from the outskirts?

36
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:18,708
Yes, from the outskirts

37
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:20,791
From the outskirts of the city

38
00:02:21,708 --> 00:02:24,500
Interviewer: The other people, about how old were they?

39
00:02:24,708 --> 00:02:27,083
Some were in their thirties and also in their twenties

40
00:02:27,666 --> 00:02:29,666
They were from their group, and they were sitting

41
00:02:30,125 --> 00:02:34,333
Interviewer: From their appearance, were they leaders or ordinary people?

42
00:02:34,416 --> 00:02:38,958
No, no, they were leaders, carrying pistols and walkie-talkies

43
00:02:39,791 --> 00:02:42,250
Interviewer: During the judge's interrogation with you?

44
00:02:42,500 --> 00:02:44,375
Regarding what was said to you directly

45
00:02:44,666 --> 00:02:48,833
Interviewer: Did any of the people there ask you a question, or was it only the judge who asked?

46
00:02:48,916 --> 00:02:52,458
No, only the judge, but later the one who sat next to the judge

47
00:02:53,208 --> 00:02:57,416
When prayer was mentioned, he told the judge that this man does not pray

48
00:02:58,041 --> 00:03:01,833
He said, It is obvious—if he prayed, made the call to prayer, and was observant

49
00:03:01,958 --> 00:03:06,166
He would not be answering this way, hesitating and making mistakes

50
00:03:07,125 --> 00:03:10,791
Interviewer: During the judge’s interrogation, was there someone next to him writing it down?

51
00:03:10,916 --> 00:03:13,541
Yes, he was writing, he was writing on a sheet of paper

52
00:03:14,250 --> 00:03:17,166
On a sheet of paper, he was writing

53
00:03:17,500 --> 00:03:22,250
For example—Why did you answer incorrectly to such and such a question?

54
00:03:22,708 --> 00:03:26,708
And your details—where you go, when you come, whom you meet, and whom you walk with

55
00:03:27,208 --> 00:03:29,875
And which grade I was in, he had a lot of information about me

56
00:03:30,333 --> 00:03:33,458
He asked me about them, and I had forgotten them, I had forgotten

57
00:03:34,166 --> 00:03:35,166
Interviewer: Like what?

58
00:03:35,291 --> 00:03:38,083
For example, he told me, You used to work

59
00:03:38,750 --> 00:03:43,166
On the road to Turkey, transporting people and bringing people, and things like that

60
00:03:43,625 --> 00:03:48,916
He asked me questions—I can tell you he was someone who knew a lot about me

61
00:03:49,541 --> 00:03:52,791
When I went in and he started talking to me, I was surprised by what he said

62
00:03:53,625 --> 00:03:55,708
Like someone who knows you personally

63
00:03:56,750 --> 00:04:02,208
Interviewer: Did he ask questions about your presence in your neighborhood?

64
00:04:02,583 --> 00:04:06,500
He asked me about my home, and about my children, how many children I have

65
00:04:06,583 --> 00:04:08,750
Married or single, and so on

66
00:04:09,041 --> 00:04:11,666
And what I have, where I go, and whom I walk with

67
00:04:12,666 --> 00:04:15,458
Even that I used to sit at my friend’s place and he had an electric generator

68
00:04:16,083 --> 00:04:19,541
He said—So you were mostly at the generator at night

69
00:04:21,250 --> 00:04:24,708
Interviewer: Did he ask about specific people to get information about them, and who were they?

70
00:04:25,083 --> 00:04:28,000
Who? No, he did not ask me that

71
00:04:28,500 --> 00:04:31,333
But I felt inside

72
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:33,916
That I was under surveillance, and he said this

73
00:04:35,625 --> 00:04:38,666
He said, This time we pardoned you, but the second time

74
00:04:39,250 --> 00:04:41,625
We will execute you immediately when we find anything against you
